From ef38ef3b2fbb6657692f0d0bef3697ff5dcef20c Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Gravio <gravio@uni-muenster.de>
Date: Fri, 24 Apr 2026 13:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] numba: add cache=True to all @jit/@njit decorators
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

User report: workbench takes 10-20s to launch every time. Profiling
points at numba JIT compilation: 121 of the 127 numba decorators in
the codebase did not have cache=True, meaning their compiled artifacts
were thrown away and regenerated from scratch on every cold start.

Fix: enable on-disk caching for every @njit/@jit decorator. Numba
writes cached artifacts to mufasa/<module>/__pycache__/ alongside
.pyc files; on subsequent imports the artifact is reused if the
source signature hasn't changed.

Coverage:
- 28 files modified
- 121 decorators got cache=True added
- 6 decorators that already had cache=True unchanged
- @cuda.jit decorators in data_processors/cuda/* not touched
  (cuda.jit doesn't support the cache parameter the same way)

Expected impact:
- First launch after install OR after editing a numba'd function:
  unchanged (compilation still has to happen once)
- All subsequent launches: noticeably faster, since previously-
  compiled artifacts on disk are reused
- No effect on runtime correctness — cache=True is a transparent
  optimization

Verification:
- All 28 modified files compile cleanly (py_compile)
- Visual inspection of representative single-line and multi-line
  decorators confirms semantically equivalent
- @cuda.jit not affected (regex matches @jit/@njit only, not
  @something.jit)

This is a mechanical edit produced by a one-shot script. The script
handles three decorator forms: bare @njit, @njit(args...) on a
single line, and @njit(\n  args...\n) across multiple lines. Files
where the parens were unbalanced (none in this codebase) would have
been left untouched.

Not in this patch:
- Lazy page construction in workbench_app.main (the bigger fix; would
  also reduce perceived startup time, but more invasive and risky)
- AOT compilation of numba functions at install time
- @cuda.jit cache support (separate per-function work, niche use)
